<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,598,767]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,375,634,659]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Main Features</emphasis>
: Hertzâ€™s variety 
<taxonomicName box="[569,688,634,659]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiolepididae" genus="Ophiosphalma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="atlanticum">
<emphasis box="[569,688,634,659]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">atlanticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dumbbell-shaped oral shields, no disc granules, and multiscaled exposed tentacle pores on the first 
<number box="[616,630,671,695]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="3.0">3</number>
segments. 
<number box="[755,769,672,695]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" value="7.0">7</number>
arm spines. The genital slits extend to the distal end of the second arm segment. The 
<typeStatus box="[445,532,707,731]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[571,731,706,731]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiolepididae" genus="Ophiomusium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="fimbriatum">
<emphasis box="[571,731,706,731]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<collectingCountry box="[571,594,707,730]" name="Iceland" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">O</collectingCountry>
. fimbriatum
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var 
<taxonomicName box="[787,905,706,731]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiolepididae" genus="Ophiosphalma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="atlanticum">
<emphasis box="[787,905,706,731]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">atlanticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
I observed in the 
<collectionCode box="[1119,1199,707,731]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mci8-ehqk" name="Zoological Museum, University of Copenhagen" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">ZMUC</collectionCode>
is 
<quantity box="[1234,1314,707,731]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="mm" value="19.0">19 mm</quantity>
d.d. I here elevate the variety to a separate species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Hertz" authorityName="Hertz" box="[605,983,742,767]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiolepididae" genus="Ophiosphalma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="atlanticum">
<emphasis box="[605,894,742,767]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Ophiosphalma atlanticum</emphasis>
(Hertz)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
